docs.summary:
At some point in the future, authenticator id will become required, for now we fall back to Wix password authenticator
option (.wix.api.required) = "LoginRequest.authenticator_id";

members.name: addressLine1
members.doc: Main address line, usually street and number as free text.

members.name: addressLine2
members.doc: Free text providing more detailed address info. Usually contains Apt, Suite, and Floor.

members.name: subdivision
members.doc: Subdivision. Usually a state, region, prefecture, or province code, according to [ISO 3166-2](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/ISO_3166-2).

members.name: entityId
members.doc: ID of the entity associated with the event.

members.name: triggeredByAnonymizeRequest
members.doc: Whether the event was triggered as a result of a privacy regulation application (for example, [GDPR](https://support.wix.com/en/article/gdpr-frequently-asked-questions)). For advanced users.

members.name: name
members.doc:
Custom field name. The name must match one of the key properties of the objects returned by
[`List Extended Fields`](https://dev.wix.com/docs/rest/api-reference/contacts/extended-fields/list-extended-fields)
with the `custom.` prefix removed.

members.name: _createdDate
members.doc: The time this identity was created.

members.name: _updatedDate
members.doc: The time this identity was last updated.

members.name: connections
members.doc: The identity configured connections to authenticate with.

members.name: metadata
members.doc:
Additional information about the identity that can impact user access.
This data cannot be set.

members.name: revision
members.doc:
Represents the current state of an item. Each time the item is modified, its `revision` changes.
For an update operation to succeed, you MUST pass the latest revision.

members.name: customFields
members.doc:
Any number of custom fields. [Custom fields](https://support.wix.com/en/article/adding-custom-fields-to-contacts)
are used to store additional information about your site or app's contacts.

members.name: state
members.doc: state that that received on the redirect

members.name: authenticatorId
members.doc: TODO: when this becomes required, it will make more sense for it to be a `string`

members.name: captchaTokens
members.doc: CAPTCHA tokens, when CAPTCHA setting is on.

members.name: password
members.doc: Password of the member logging in.

members.name: idpConnectionId
members.doc: The id of the connection id (can be fetched by calling connection-service.listEnabledConnectionsClientData

members.name: sessionId
members.doc:
This flow ultimately returns an HTML page that asynchronously posts the LoginResponse via the BroadcastChannel API.
The message will be posted to a channel named `wix-idp-$session_id`, and encrypted with the `encryption_key`.
Encryption key should be base64 encoded. Encryption is done using AES-GCM with a random IV that's sent alongside the payload

members.name: tenantId
members.doc: The id of the tenant the caller wants to login into

members.name: tenantType
members.doc: The type of the tenant the caller wants to login into

members.name: idpConnectionId
members.doc: The id of the connection id (can be fetched by calling connection-service.listEnabledConnectionsClientData

members.name: params
members.doc: A set of fields that are required for the connection to be able to identify and authenticate the user

members.name: stateToken
members.doc: State token received from the previous step in the registration or login process.

members.name: authenticatorId
members.doc: TODO: when this becomes required, it will make more sense for it to be a `string`

members.name: captchaTokens
members.doc: CAPTCHA tokens, when CAPTCHA setting is on.

members.name: mergeExistingContact
members.doc: when false will create a new contact instead of merging the existing contact into the identity

members.name: verifyEmail
members.doc: when true will mark the email of the identity as verified

members.name: sessionToken
members.doc: session token for the requested identity

members.name: sessionToken
members.doc: If state is `SUCCESS`, a session token.

members.name: state
members.doc: The current state of the login or registration process.

members.name: stateToken
members.doc: A token representing the current state of the login or registration process.
